        tangent lines to each of the two graphs at the point <m>x = 0</m>?
        <m>x = 1</m>? <m>x = 2</m>? or <m>x = a</m>,
        where <m>a</m> is some other constant?
      </p>

      <image>

<latex-image>
          <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}[xscale=0.5, yscale=0.5]
        \draw [style={gray, thick}] (0,0) grid (16,16);
        \draw [<->, style={black, very thick}] (8,0) -- (8,16);
        \draw [<->, style={black, very thick}] (0,8) -- (16,8);
        \node at (15.5, 8.5){\(x\)};
        \node at (8.5, 15.5){\(y\)};\end{tikzpicture}]]>
</latex-image>
